.TH "cpuidle_setup_broadcast_timer" 9 "cpuidle_setup_broadcast_timer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_setup_broadcast_timer \- enable/disable the broadcast timer on a cpu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" cpuidle_setup_broadcast_timer
.BI "(void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "arg" 12
a void pointer used to match the SMP cross call API
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If \fIarg\fP is NULL broadcast is disabled otherwise enabled

This function is executed per CPU by an SMP cross call.  It's not
supposed to be called directly.
